# 📘 COMPLETE GUIDE: Unattended Windows Deployment Using ADK + Windows SIM

---

# 🧭 OVERVIEW

This guide teaches how to build a **fully automated Windows installation media** using:

* Windows ADK (Assessment and Deployment Kit)
* Windows System Image Manager (SIM)
* DISM (Deployment Image Servicing and Management)

By the end, you will have:

✔ Automated installation (no user interaction)
✔ Automatic disk partitioning (UEFI + BIOS)
✔ Preloaded drivers
✔ Preconfigured system settings
✔ Automatic user account creation

---

# 🧰 PART 1 — INSTALLATION OF REQUIRED TOOLS

## 1.1 Install Windows ADK

Download and install:

* Windows ADK
* Windows PE Add-on

During installation, select:

Deployment Tools
Windows System Image Manager (SIM)

---

# 📁 PART 2 — PREPARE WORKING ENVIRONMENT

Create a structured workspace:

C:\WinLab
├── ISO
├── Mount
├── Drivers
├── Catalog
└── Unattend\

---

## 2.1 Extract Windows ISO

Mount or extract your Windows ISO into:

C:\WinLab\ISO\

You should see:

sources
boot
efi
setup.exe

---

# 🧱 PART 3 — CREATE CATALOG FILE (.CLG)

## 3.1 Open Windows SIM

Launch:
Windows System Image Manager

---

## 3.2 Load Windows Image

File → Select Windows Image

Navigate to:

C:\WinLab\ISO\sources\install.wim

Select your desired edition (e.g., Windows 11 Pro).

---

## 3.3 Generate Catalog

If prompted:

"Create catalog file?" → YES

This creates:

install.clg

⚠️ This step may take several minutes.

---

# 📄 PART 4 — CREATE ANSWER FILE (AUTOUNATTEND.XML)

## 4.1 Create New File

File → New Answer File

---

# ⚙️ CONFIGURATION PASSES EXPLAINED

windowsPE → Pre-install (disk, language, setup)
specialize → System configuration
oobeSystem → User setup and first boot

---

# ⚙️ PART 5 — CONFIGURE windowsPE PASS

## 5.1 Add Required Components

Add to windowsPE:

Microsoft-Windows-International-Core-WinPE
Microsoft-Windows-Setup

---

## 5.2 Configure Language

Set:

InputLocale = en-US
SystemLocale = en-US
UILanguage = en-US
UserLocale = en-US

---

## 5.3 Configure Disk (AUTO FORMAT)

Right-click Microsoft-Windows-Setup → Add DiskConfiguration

---

### Disk Settings

DiskID = 0
WillWipeDisk = true

---

## 5.4 Create Partitions (UEFI - GPT)

CreatePartitions:

Order 1 → EFI → 100MB
Order 2 → MSR → 16MB
Order 3 → Primary → Extend = true

---

## 5.5 Modify Partitions

Partition 1:
Format = FAT32
Label = System

Partition 3:
Format = NTFS
Letter = C
Label = Windows

---

## 5.6 Configure OS Installation Target

ImageInstall → OSImage → InstallTo:

DiskID = 0
PartitionID = 3

---

## 5.7 Accept License

UserData:

AcceptEula = true
FullName = Admin
Organization = Lab

---

# 🧩 PART 6 — CONFIGURE specialize PASS

## 6.1 Add Component

Microsoft-Windows-Shell-Setup → specialize

---

## 6.2 Configure System

ComputerName = AUTO-PC
TimeZone = Romance Standard Time

---

# 👤 PART 7 — CONFIGURE oobeSystem PASS

## 7.1 Add Component

Microsoft-Windows-Shell-Setup → oobeSystem

---

## 7.2 Configure OOBE (Skip Setup Screens)

HideEULAPage = true
HideWirelessSetupInOOBE = true
ProtectYourPC = 1
NetworkLocation = Work

---

## 7.3 Create User Accounts

UserAccounts → LocalAccounts → Add

---

### Admin User

Name = admin
Group = Administrators
Password = Admin123!
PlainText = true

---

### Standard User

Name = user
Group = Users
Password = User123!
PlainText = true

---

## 7.4 Configure Auto Logon

Username = admin
Enabled = true
LogonCount = 1
Password = Admin123!

---

# 💾 PART 8 — SAVE ANSWER FILE

Save as:

C:\WinLab\ISO\autounattend.xml

---

# ✅ PART 9 — VALIDATE CONFIGURATION

In SIM:

Tools → Validate Answer File

Fix all errors before proceeding.

---

# 🔌 PART 10 — DRIVER INJECTION (DISM)

## 10.1 Mount Image

dism /Mount-Wim /WimFile:C:\WinLab\ISO\sources\install.wim /index:6 /MountDir:C:\WinLab\Mount

---

## 10.2 Inject Drivers

dism /Image:C:\WinLab\Mount /Add-Driver /Driver:C:\WinLab\Drivers /Recurse

---

## 10.3 Commit Changes

dism /Unmount-Wim /MountDir:C:\WinLab\Mount /Commit

---

# 💿 PART 11 — CREATE BOOTABLE USB

## 11.1 Prepare USB

diskpart

list disk
select disk X
clean
create partition primary
format fs=fat32 quick
active
assign
exit

---

## 11.2 Copy Installation Files

xcopy C:\WinLab\ISO* X:\ /E /H

---

# 🧠 PART 12 — BIOS vs UEFI EXPLANATION

## UEFI (Modern Systems)

* Uses GPT partitioning
* Requires EFI partition
* Supports Secure Boot

---

## BIOS (Legacy Systems)

* Uses MBR
* Requires active primary partition
* No EFI partition

---

## Teaching Tip

Have students compare:

UEFI layout:
EFI + MSR + Primary

BIOS layout:
Single Primary (Active)

---

